item.title: CVE-2022-3834|2024-08-03T01:20:58.477Z -- unknown -- google%20forms
item.description: The Google Forms WordPress plugin through 0.95 does not sanitise and escape some of its settings, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup).
